HOW IS THE STAGING AREA DIFFERENT FROM THE WORKING DIRECTORY
AND THE REPOSITORY? WHAT VALUE DO YOU THINK IT OFFERS?

The staging area allows you to choose which files you would
like to commit. Often times you might be working a few files
at once but only require one file to be commited at this
point. It's value is it's ability to know exactly which files
you are going to commit. You have more control on what your
putting into the next commit and repository.

How can you use the staging area to make sure you have one 
commit per logical change?

You push through only the files that are part of the
single logical change that you are making.

